text: Coffee River Cave is a large river cave in Manchester Parish in west-central Jamaica. It is in length and at an elevation of . ==Natural history== The cave is a large bat roost, and some bat guano is harvested from the outer regions of the cave. ==See also== *List of caves#Jamaica *Jamaican Caves Organisation *Manchester Parish, Jamaica ==References== ==External links== *Aerial view *Photos: *Video: *Coffee River Cave - Jamaican Caves Organisation Category:Bat roosts Category:Caves of Jamaica Category:Geography of Manchester Parish Category:Caves of the Caribbean
